	affiliations = {Hampton University, Hampton, United States},
	abstract = {The unit operations laboratory (lab) in chemical engineering offers a unique learning experience where seniors are exposed to real-world chemical processes. They get hands-on activity on laboratory scaled industrial equipment and better insight into chemical engineering fundamentals that they learned in their sophomore and junior years. In these labs, the students work in groups to conduct the experiment, collect and analyze data, and finally write and present their technical reports. Thus these labs helped toned students' ability to collaborate and improve their writing and oral skills. The problem-solving skills, a core competency skill for an engineering student, do not seem to be much appreciated through these unit labs. To rectify the situation and take full advantage of the unit lab in making the students' problem solvers, we taught the class in a hybrid approach mixing the traditional Model of classroom instruction with the flipped classroom model over a semester. During a semester, students performed three-unit laboratory experiments. Two of them were taught in a traditional way: the instructor provided the background and standard operating procedures for the instrument of that particular experiment. Then, the students in groups conducted the experiment under the instructor's supervision. The third remaining unit laboratory was taught in a flipped classroom model. Each group gathers the background information about the particular laboratory they were assigned to and figured out the working of the instrument by themselves by going over the manual and concept from the book and other online resources in detail. For the first two labs, they were tested by the submission of the individual laboratory report at the end of the experiment. While for the third experiment, in addition to the complete group lab report, each group was assessed every week on building different sections of the report, including objectives and introduction, theory, materials, s